  "body": "### Component\n\nForge\n\n### Describe the feature you would like\n\nI would like forge to generate Rust enums of the following Solidity code:\r\n\r\n```solidity\r\npragma solidity ^0.8.13;\r\n\r\ncontract Foo {\r\n    enum Bar {\r\n        A,\r\n        B,\r\n        C\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    function doSomething(Foo foo) public view {}\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nThe above should generate something like this:\r\n\r\n```rust\r\n#[derive(Debug, Clone, Copy)]\r\n#[repr(u8)]\r\nenum Bar {\r\n    A,\r\n    B,\r\n    C,\r\n}\r\n\r\nimpl Bar {\r\n    fn from_u8(val: u8) -> Option<Bar> {\r\n        match val {\r\n            0 => Some(Bar::A),\r\n            1 => Some(Bar::B),\r\n            2 => Some(Bar::C),\r\n            _ => None,\r\n        }\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    fn to_u8(&self) -> u8 {\r\n        *self as u8\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n```\n\n### Additional context\n\nAs I understand this is a limitation because only the `abi` field is used from the json file.\r\n\r\nThis information can be retrieved from `ast` field, but `abigen` does not accept this kind of input.",
