    "body": "I don't think enum variants are included in the abi itself.\r\n\r\n```solidity\r\ncontract Foo {\r\n    enum Bar {\r\n        A,\r\n        B,\r\n        C\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    function doSomething(Bar bar) public view {}\r\n}\r\n\r\n```\r\n\r\n```json\r\n\t\"abi\": [\r\n\t\t{\r\n\t\t\t\"inputs\": [\r\n\t\t\t\t{\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\"internalType\": \"enum Foo.Bar\",\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\"name\": \"bar\",\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\"type\": \"uint8\"\r\n\t\t\t\t}\r\n\t\t\t],\r\n\t\t\t\"name\": \"doSomething\",\r\n\t\t\t\"outputs\": [],\r\n\t\t\t\"stateMutability\": \"view\",\r\n\t\t\t\"type\": \"function\"\r\n\t\t}\r\n\t]\r\n\r\n```\r\n\r\nso we only know that there's an enum but don't know anything about the variants",
